Package de.db.derpate.servlet

Class BaseServlet

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.servlet.GenericServlet
      • javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
        • de.db.derpate.servlet.BaseServlet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FilterServlet, RedirectServlet
    public abstract class BaseServlet
extends javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet
    This abstract HttpServlet should be used for all created servlets, as it sets the character encoding and stops request, if request or response is null.
    Supported Methods: GET, POST, DELETE
    Author:
    MichelBlank
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
